    <briefdescription>
<para>Abstract base class for stack nodes. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The <ref refid="classBULKCC_1_1Obj" kindref="compound">Obj</ref> class is the abstract base class for all stack nodes in the <ref refid="namespaceBULKCC" kindref="compound">BULKCC</ref> library. It provides the fundamental linked-list structure for storing objects in a stack.</para>
<sect1 id="classBULKCC_1_1Obj_1design">
<title>Design</title>
<para>Each stack node contains:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>A pointer to the next node in the stack (_nextObj)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Virtual methods for type identification and object management</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>This class cannot be instantiated directly. Use ObjTemplate&lt;T&gt; to create concrete stack nodes that can store objects of a specific type.</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="group__BULKCC_1usage">
<title>Basic Usage</title>
<para>This class is typically not used directly. Instead, use the <ref refid="classBULKCC_1_1Controller" kindref="compound">Controller</ref> class to manage stacks:</para>
<para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="classBULKCC_1_1Controller" kindref="compound">BULKCC::Controller</ref><sp/>controller;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="classBULKCC_1_1Obj" kindref="compound">BULKCC::Obj</ref>*<sp/>stack<sp/>=<sp/>controller.<ref refid="classBULKCC_1_1Controller_1a20c5e4e20cc7b8f7cf5a5c8f0375327a" kindref="member">add</ref>&lt;MyType*&gt;(myObject);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classBULKCC_1_1Controller" kindref="compound">Controller</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classBULKCC_1_1ObjTemplate" kindref="compound">ObjTemplate</ref> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
</sect1>
    </detaileddescription>
